    public interface NamedParticipant<I extends Interaction,​F extends Feature>
extends Participant<I,​F>
    A named entity is an entity having a short name and a fullname in addition to aliases. The shortname is used for displaying the entity and the fullname is the description of the entity.
    Since:
    13/11/13
